    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions at Gradation 2 versus the required Gradation 3 — is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to ASTM F1717 quasi-static conditions, the model influence is rated Medium, and the overall validation evidence (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs, N=11 specimens across two laboratories) provides sufficient confidence for the intended regulatory submission context.",
